{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"a8418276-f09a-4125-b154-084d8f0e17d7","content":"Your `.testsettings` configures two things: **assembly resolution** (load from test directory) and a **30s test timeout**. In MSTest v3, `.testsettings` is ignored — you migrate these to a `.runsettings` file.\n\nHere's the migration:","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"tooluse_ZimFJ66nia30vayzODzC7Z","name":"report_intent","arguments":{"intent":"Migrating testsettings to runsettings"},"type":"function"},{"toolCallId":"tooluse_phdmhgcoBsuHdfXUuZNHVh","name":"create","arguments":{"path":"/tmp/sv-a5406009f1eb4f06aa4416626006ecc2/local.runsettings","file_text":"<?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?>\n<RunSettings>\n  <MSTest>\n    <!-- Replaces TestTimeout from .testsettings (30 seconds) -->\n    <TestTimeout>30000</TestTimeout>\n    <!-- Assembly resolution with useLoadContext is the default behavior in v3 -->\n    <DeploymentEnabled>false</DeploymentEnabled>\n  </MSTest>\n</RunSettings>\n"},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"create a new file at /tmp/sv-a5406009f1eb4f06aa4416626006ecc2/local.runsettings."},{"toolCallId":"tooluse_cX7JGEsiVK5VmcCwMUpCnk","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/tmp/sv-a5406009f1eb4f06aa4416626006ecc2/TestProject.csproj","old_str":"  <PropertyGroup>\n    <TargetFramework>net8.0</TargetFramework>\n  </PropertyGroup>","new_str":"  <PropertyGroup>\n    <TargetFramework>net8.0</TargetFramework>\n    <RunSettingsFilePath>$(MSBuildProjectDirectory)\\local.runsettings</RunSettingsFilePath>\n  </PropertyGroup>"},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"edit the file at /tmp/sv-a5406009f1eb4f06aa4416626006ecc2/TestProject.csproj."}],"interactionId":"6339eee1-3619-428c-8700-da089fbaeaa0","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user has a `.testsettings` file that configures:\n1. Assembly resolution with `useLoadContext=\"true\"`\n2. A test timeout of 30000ms (30 seconds)\n\nIn MSTest v3, `.testsettings` files are no longer supported. The migration path is to use a `.runsettings` file instead.\n\nLet me create a `.runsettings` file that replaces the `.testsettings` configuration:\n\n1. **TestTimeout** → `<TestTimeout>30000</TestTimeout>` under `<MSTest>` section in `.runsettings`\n2. **Assembly resolution / deployment** → `<DeploymentEnabled>false</DeploymentEnabled>` or configure deployment in `.runsettings`. The `useLoadContext=\"true\"` basically means \"load from the test directory\" which is the default behavior in modern MSTest anyway.\n\n\nNow I'll write out the `.runsettings` file with the timeout configuration and update the project file to reference it.","outputTokens":743},"id":"055f083a-0f39-479f-92c6-0e939deb8f5b","timestamp":"2026-04-05T01:00:12.290Z","parentId":"13806c1a-a8c6-40bd-8b9f-4f9af6fe6ae3"}
